Flames shot from Thassalin's jaws as the huge Thraki set a particular section of the forest ablaze and then circled overhead to detect movement. Strangely enough, the eerie screeching behind him ceased as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten the passengers on his back.
"What's this, Tenuk, you've already transformed into a Thraki before!"
"It's entirely different when I fly myself, than being suddenly lifted up by a huge pink dragon!"
"It wasn't that bad, was it, Kayel?"
Kayel was obviously not in agreement with Nyssi's opinion. He looked less black than usual and his claws had dug so deeply into Thassalin's back that the Thraki bled. Thassalin apparently didn't care about this. Nevertheless, he had realized he had scared his new friends and landed in a clearing.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I SWEPT SOMETHING UP. I HAD TO TAKE CARE OF IT!"
"But did you have to drag us along too?" growled Tenuk as he climbed down from Thassalin's back and slid down the tail. "And we left Retvik behind! We've abandoned our big, strong fighter! How on earth will he catch up with us?"
"He'll think of something...," growled Nyssi. "Retvik isn't the fastest, but he's not dumb."
"Well, can Retvik drive?"
Nyssi winked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he can drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik drive a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I haven't even seen him drive a nice little car like Kayel's. Besides, he only started taking the car for work because you always drive us. He only has his bicycle."
Loud laughter interrupted her. Thassalin suddenly found something incredibly funny, but nobody knew what he was laughing about. It took a bit too long for Thassalin to calm down.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR GIANT FRIEND ARMORED UP ON SUCH A TINY LITTLE BIKE FOR TEMTHAN KIDS. THAT WAS HILARIOUS! I WISH I HAD SOME KIND OF TELEPATHY. A FANTASTIC IMAGINATION! ONE I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel chuckled, as he could imagine what was going on in Thassalin's mind. "Yeah, that's true. But what did you smell, and why did you suddenly take off?"
Thassalin grunted, lifted off, and vanished. When he returned shortly after, he threw something lifeless in front of Nyssi's feet. It was an Orothrack, a very rare, gold-white dragon creature. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEAD ONE. I HEAR THEIR SCREAMS. SMELL THEIR BLOOD. SOMETHING DRIVES ME TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI COMMANDS. THEY ARE VERY CLOSE."
The mighty Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel also froze and looked attentively toward a gap in the clearing. Something large and black stared at them and hissed. Whatever it was, it spread out two enormous pairs of wings and shot toward Thassalin, without caring about the three smaller beings between them. Kayel and Tenuk could just barely take cover, but Nyssi was dragged along and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to this attack by grabbing Nyssi and hurling him onto his back with his incredibly long, skillful tail before he himself took to the air. The black, double-winged creature pursued them at high speed.
Kayel snapped annoyed while he took his rifle from his back and opened a bag containing a ammunition belt. He slung the belt over his chest, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were out of sight.
“Hey, Tenuk, could you transform into something that can fly?”, asked Kayel.
“You want to follow them?”
"Yes, of course!"
"But... One of them is a huge monster!"
"Yes and? I'm standing here with a top-notch rifle in my hand and could shoot right away. But, well, how should I say – I would have to be able to see it in order to hit it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to have more room. With a soft, painful grumble, Tenuk's body stretched out, his fur turned into scales and his arms into wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, bright blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Looking like an ordinary Thraki, Tenuk now had a proper scaly shield running along his back. Conveniently, he had also grown a pair of spines on his back, allowing Kayel to hold on. It took a little too long for Tenuk to get the flight started, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and tried to catch up.
Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they were not alone. A second dark creature shot up beneath them, and Tenuk could only narrowly avoid a collision.
"That must be the other terrifying giant monster that Lanex was afraid of?" Kayel furrowed his brow. He tried to shoot at the second beast, missed, and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk did not answer. He was too busy focusing on the flight towards Nyssi and Thassalin, although the other creature was pursuing them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to keep the monster in view. The fact that it was following them was an advantage for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and fire. Two shots went through the upper wings of the creature. It screamed in pain and sank back beneath the trees. Kayel was not sure if it was still following them, but it certainly would not be able to keep up with them.
A good distance ahead, Nyssi was desperately clinging on, while Thassalin was flailing around and spitting fireballs at the blackened monster. The creature was definitely injured. It seemed extremely angry, but not ready to give in. The fireballs did not seem to have the desired effect. As Thassalin stretched, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw her own weapon, a good old shot gun. It was not exactly the first choice, but maybe the shot would scare off the black beast.
